item.title: My silabsoft won't work
item.dc:creator: @_M_ose ~M°ose~
item.description:
@_M_ose wrote:

No, KillSwitch is trying to act “Java Smart”, You do not need Moparscape Aryan for Silabs Client, Seeing as Silabs client is a client and it already has its basic Rs models in it and the ones added by Silab. And the only way it could “Feed” off of it is it was in the same folder or you had an uplink of somesort. So KillSwitch, Learn the basics before you try to help people. One of the reason that he may not be able to run his client may be because of Enviromental Variables : CLASSPATH and Path.

item.title: My silabsoft won't work
item.dc:creator: @KillSwitchScape KillSwitchScape
item.description:
@KillSwitchScape wrote:

You need moparscape 3.2 W/ Aryan to run Silabs… It feeds off of it for the other models which are all on moparscape. Without it you get an error.
